1. Convert each character of the string to its corresponding integer value using ASCII values.
2. Calculate the sum of the integers.
3. Calculate the result by multiplying the sum with the base of the modulus (10^9 + 7) and taking the remainder.
4. Iterate through the array of integers and multiply each element with the base of the modulus and the current element, and take the remainder.
5. Return the final result.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n) because it iterates through the string once. The space complexity is O(n) because it uses a vector to store the integer values of the string elements. The energy implications are low because the algorithm is efficient and does not require any complex operations.

